<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="238" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1481,1940]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1481,1507]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Adult males differ from all other species of the genus by the combination of the following characters: presence of a wide lateral expansion in the solenomere (
<figureCitation box="[775,877,1517,1543]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-20@39.[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Abiliodesmus defensor (Hoffman, 1976) comb. nov. (holotype, MZSP 1067), dorsal views of anterior (A), midbody (B) and posterior (C) body rings. Scale bars: 2 mm. Left gonopod. (D), mesal view; (E), ventral view; (F), ectal view. Scale bars: 0,5 mm. Abbreviations: C, cingulum; PfP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761625/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 22D</figureCitation>
) and the prefemoral process completely involving the solenomere, in ectal view (
<figureCitation box="[494,594,1553,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-20@39.[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Abiliodesmus defensor (Hoffman, 1976) comb. nov. (holotype, MZSP 1067), dorsal views of anterior (A), midbody (B) and posterior (C) body rings. Scale bars: 2 mm. Left gonopod. (D), mesal view; (E), ventral view; (F), ectal view. Scale bars: 0,5 mm. Abbreviations: C, cingulum; PfP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761625/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 22F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1481,1940]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1589,1615]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[427,536,1589,1615]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Holotype</typeStatus>
, MZSP 1067). Coloration (long-preserved in 70% ethanol): Head and antennae ochre (both antennae of the 
<typeStatus box="[472,570,1625,1651]" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">holotype</typeStatus>
are broken). Body ocher with the edges of the paranota whitish (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-20@39.[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Abiliodesmus defensor (Hoffman, 1976) comb. nov. (holotype, MZSP 1067), dorsal views of anterior (A), midbody (B) and posterior (C) body rings. Scale bars: 2 mm. Left gonopod. (D), mesal view; (E), ventral view; (F), ectal view. Scale bars: 0,5 mm. Abbreviations: C, cingulum; PfP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761625/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Figs 22A– C</figureCitation>
). Legs ocher yellowish. Telson ocher. Total length: 34.63. Total width: 5.26. Collum, length 1.39, width 4.62. Antennomere lengths (1&gt;7): 0.46; 1.28; 1.09; 1.17; 1.18; 1.10; 0.34. Podomeres lengths (1&gt;7): 0.55; 0.70; 1.74; 0.68; 0.79; 1.27; 0.39. Gonopod aperture, length 1.03, width 1.68. Telson, length 0.93. Gonopod: length 1.99, width 0.94. Gonocoxae: length 0.58, width 0.29. Telopodite: length 1.99, width 0.65. Prefemoral process long (slightly larger than the solenomere) and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[620,724,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-20@39.[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Abiliodesmus defensor (Hoffman, 1976) comb. nov. (holotype, MZSP 1067), dorsal views of anterior (A), midbody (B) and posterior (C) body rings. Scale bars: 2 mm. Left gonopod. (D), mesal view; (E), ventral view; (F), ectal view. Scale bars: 0,5 mm. Abbreviations: C, cingulum; PfP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761625/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 22E</figureCitation>
). Solenomere long with a lateral membranous expansion (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-20@39.[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Abiliodesmus defensor (Hoffman, 1976) comb. nov. (holotype, MZSP 1067), dorsal views of anterior (A), midbody (B) and posterior (C) body rings. Scale bars: 2 mm. Left gonopod. (D), mesal view; (E), ventral view; (F), ectal view. Scale bars: 0,5 mm. Abbreviations: C, cingulum; PfP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761625/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 22D</figureCitation>
). Cingulum in basal position (
<figureCitation box="[541,641,1841,1867]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-20@39.[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Abiliodesmus defensor (Hoffman, 1976) comb. nov. (holotype, MZSP 1067), dorsal views of anterior (A), midbody (B) and posterior (C) body rings. Scale bars: 2 mm. Left gonopod. (D), mesal view; (E), ventral view; (F), ectal view. Scale bars: 0,5 mm. Abbreviations: C, cingulum; PfP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761625/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Fig. 22F</figureCitation>
). Apex of the solenomere acuminate and ascending (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1339,1841,1867]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetId="figure-20@39.[161,1426,181,1680]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 22. Abiliodesmus defensor (Hoffman, 1976) comb. nov. (holotype, MZSP 1067), dorsal views of anterior (A), midbody (B) and posterior (C) body rings. Scale bars: 2 mm. Left gonopod. (D), mesal view; (E), ventral view; (F), ectal view. Scale bars: 0,5 mm. Abbreviations: C, cingulum; PfP, prefemoral process; S, solenomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4761625" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4761625/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="238">Figs 22D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
